The paper discusses a path loss model for wireless transmissions in small cell networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also analyzes coverage probability and achievable rate, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses blockage effects and fading scenarios, which are related to signal processing (cs.SI) and computer engineering (cs.CE).
